Description:
Ballistics of APFSDS-T rounds fired from the Type 71 120mm smoothbore tank gun. Projectiles either of Tungsten-core-steel-sheath, or steel rod construction. Projectiles weigh 4.3 kg.

Charge:               8.4 kg 
Muzzle Velocity:      1580 m/s
Cartridge Length:     790 mm
Chambrage:            1.33-1.34 (estimated)

Web ratio adjusted to more accurately model behavior of mixed charge.
References:
- 陆祥璇《“两炮”火力系统总体论证》, referenced as "Old 120mm", noting 8.244 kg charge (5.952 kg 11/7 Rosette main + 1.0kg 12/1-420 bundle + 1.292 kg 11/7 Rosette filling around fins) developing peak breech pressure of 318.6 MPa (or 318.7 MPa), likely converting from copper crusher gauge measurement at face value, without conversion.
- 《火炸药手册（增订本）第二分册 固体火箭推进剂和枪炮发射药》presents an alternative interpretation, noting 8.4 kg (9/7 + 18/1 + 12/1 Rosium-Potassium) charge and developing 3280 kgf/cm^2 (copper crusher gauge value, converts to 360.2 MPa piezoelectric with factor of 1.12 * 0.098) peak breech pressure.
Entry reflects compromise between sources that best reflect gun design best practices.
